Which of the following configuration lines will set the DNS server to 192.168.1.4 using /etc/resolv.conf?
A)  dns 168.1.4
B)  dns- server 168.1.4
C)  nameserver 168.1.4
D)  name- server 168.1.4
C
C. The configuration option is nameserver, and the value for the option is the IP addressof the desired name server. Several options affect how name resolution is performed, such asthe number of attempts and timeout. See resolv.conf(5) for more information.
